Restaurant App Demo Privacy Policy
1. Introduction
Welcome to Restaurant App! We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you use our restaurant services and mobile app. By using our services, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
2. Information We Collect
•  Personal Information: When you make reservations, order food, or interact with our mobile app, we may collect personal information such as your name, contact details, and payment information.
•  Location Information: We may collect your device's location data to provide restaurant recommendations and assist with food delivery services.
•  Usage Data: We collect data about how you interact with our app, including the pages you visit, the items you order, and your preferences.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your information for the following purposes:
•  To process reservations, orders, and payments.
•  To personalize your experience and provide restaurant recommendations.
•  To communicate with you about your reservations and orders.
•  To improve our services and offerings.
•  To send you marketing and promotional materials with your consent.
4. Data Sharing
We may share your information with:
•  Third-Party Service Providers: We may use third-party services for payment processing, analytics, and marketing. These service providers are bound by confidentiality and data protection agreements.
•  Legal Obligations: We may share your information to comply with legal requirements or protect our rights, property, or safety.
5. Data Security
We take data security seriously and employ appropriate measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
6. Your Rights
•  Access: You have the right to access the personal information we hold about you.
•  Rectification: You can request corrections to inaccuracies in your data.
•  Deletion: You may request the deletion of your data, subject to legal and operational requirements.
•  Data Portability: You can request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used format.
•  Consent Withdrawal: You have the right to withdraw consent for marketing communications.
7. Cookies and Tracking
We use cookies and similar technologies to enhance your browsing experience. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
8. Children's Privacy
Our services are not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
9. Changes to Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our data practices. Please review this policy periodically for updates.
10. Contact Us
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at +971 545220022.
